    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for gstreamer1-plugins-ugly-free.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "GStreamer is a streaming media framework, based on graphs of elements which operate on media data.  This package contains plug-ins whose license is not fully compatible with LGPL.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* gstreamer1-plugins-ugly-free: GStreamer: Out-of-bounds read in RealMedia demuxer audio stream header parser (CVE-2026-53703)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      },
      {
